parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the vehicle's computer system can cause the car to become uncontrollable, leading to accidents, damage, and potential harm to the driver and others.
symptoms: The car accelerates or brakes suddenly without input from the driver
the car does not respond to the brakes or ignition
the car's automatic emergency braking
forward collision
or parking collision systems fail to function.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the high voltage lithium-ion battery can cause the car to malfunction, leading to safety risks, including the potential for fires.
symptoms: Loud buzzing or vibration sounds coming from the battery area
the battery not achieving full charge
the battery gauge showing low levels of charge
fear of overheating or fire.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the collision mitigation system can cause the car to brake suddenly or fail to brake, leading to accidents, damage, and potential harm to the driver and others.
symptoms: The collision mitigation system brake warning flashes and brakes suddenly
the car stops responding to the accelerator
the lane departure feature malfunctions
pulling the car into oncoming traffic.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the hybrid system can cause the car to fail to achieve its intended fuel efficiency, leading to decreased performance and potential safety risks.
symptoms: The gas engine runs the car 90% of the time
the EV motor rarely comes on
the high voltage battery gauge always shows low levels of charge
the car fails to achieve its intended fuel efficiency.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of tires with thin sidewalls can lead to sudden loss of control, accidents, or rollovers, especially at higher speeds.
symptoms: Multiple tires blow out simultaneously
especially on the passenger side
after hitting potholes or other road hazards.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A malfunctioning TPMS can lead to incorrect warnings, causing driver distraction, anxiety, and potentially delayed reaction to actual tire pressure issues.
symptoms: False warnings of low tire pressure
despite correct tire pressure
causing unnecessary concern and potential safety risks.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Sudden wheel rim failure can cause loss of control, accidents, or rollovers, especially at higher speeds.
symptoms: Loud noise
difficulty balancing the vehicle
and wheel rim damage without any apparent impact or object strike.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the power steering assist can cause the steering wheel to become difficult to turn, leading to loss of control and increased risk of accidents, especially on the highway.
symptoms: The steering wheel becomes difficult to turn
the steering wheel sticks at a certain position (e.g.
12 o'clock)
the steering wheel requires significant pressure to turn
the vehicle jerks or pulls to one side when the steering wheel finally breaks free.
